If you cannot unlock your session
just access to tty2 and then

sudo loginctl unlock-session 2

or to unlock all the session:
sudo loginctl unlock-sessions

the exit with ctrl+d
and go back to tty1

with

ctrl + alt +f1


You can also list all the sessions with:

loginctl list-sessions 

REMEMBER with the italian keyboard you may need to use: 'altgr + -' to get the dash symbol '-'
